[{"question":"Plus was Whitney\u0027s fame simply too much for her to bear?","answer":"Fame in itself is an addictive drug and also fame creates an image which you cannot live up to.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":5,"aSentId":6},{"question":"What did he tell you?","answer":"I did, Piers.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":29,"aSentId":30},{"question":"Another thing that he wanted to talk about that I asked him about, you know, that whole thing, Piers, about Mickey Fine, the pharmacist that was involved with the Michael Jackson case?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":38,"aSentId":39},{"question":"What do you know about that?","answer":"EMON: Yes.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":55,"aSentId":56},{"question":"What were you reacting to?","answer":"Fans being robbed.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":75,"aSentId":76},{"question":"Do you think there is any duty if you have a star of the magnitude of a Whitney Houston to give the fans something though?","answer":"I mean that\u0027s -- I mean she gave the fans something, she gave them her amazing music, her amazing voice through her records that will be there forever, the best performances of all time.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":79,"aSentId":80},{"question":"When did you hear the news of Whitney\u0027s death?","answer":"I heard it Saturday.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":84,"aSentId":85},{"question":"What do you think -- knowing her as you do, what do you think?","answer":"You know, I wasn\u0027t around her all the time.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":101,"aSentId":102},{"question":"How did she seem to you, Whitney?","answer":"I mean, you know, when I\u0027ve seen her, she\u0027s always really a very up person, she\u0027s so full of life.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":113,"aSentId":114},{"question":"I\u0027m sorry?","answer":"Is it right to apportion any blame or do you think --","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":162,"aSentId":163},{"question":"And Chaka Khan -- could you imagine that she just would instinctively rail against anyone that tried to tell her what to do?","answer":"You know I have a feeling that she did what she wanted to do, you know, in working with her.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":191,"aSentId":192},{"question":"What did you feel?","answer":"You know, it wasn\u0027t -- I mean, it was weird, yes.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":202,"aSentId":203},{"question":"What do you think?","answer":"HOPRA: It\u0027s a very complex issue, Piers.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":239,"aSentId":240},{"question":"I mean when they become fabulously famous, rich, successful, and they start getting into this whole drug scene, illegal and legal, do you see a change in them?","answer":"So I don\u0027t see a lot of -- I don\u0027t usually hang out with a lot of the artists I work with, so I don\u0027t see a lot of that.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":261,"aSentId":262},{"question":"How do you treat an addiction to fame?","answer":"You have to realize, first of all, that fame actually causes the same brain chemical changes as a drug does.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":317,"aSentId":318},{"question":"How is she doing?","answer":"Piers, I\u0027m not at liberty to talk about that right now.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":326,"aSentId":327},{"question":"When you worked with her, were you aware of all these struggles she was going through?","answer":"I think that any singer that sings as amazing as she sung, when you have a certain pain that you can touch people, that you\u0027re carrying a pain with you.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":358,"aSentId":359},{"question":"What went wrong?","answer":"She obviously led a very tortured life.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":374,"aSentId":375},{"question":"But her instinctive reaction would be to rail against whatever you wanted?","answer":"To take some direction, but, you know, you can\u0027t have conversations with people when they\u0027re stars about certain things.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":412,"aSentId":413},{"question":"What do you think?","answer":"I think she was vulnerable.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":427,"aSentId":428},{"question":"How did she react to that afterwards?","answer":"We talked about it later, when -- the first time I visited her at her house.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":451,"aSentId":452},{"question":"She had -- how good was her voice at its best?","answer":"Better than anybody on the planet.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":470,"aSentId":471},{"question":"Literally?","answer":"For me.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":472,"aSentId":473},{"question":"Has there ever been a better recording voice?","answer":"I always say she was the best singer ever.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":475,"aSentId":476},{"question":"Do you know how she felt about it?","answer":"Didn\u0027t really talk about it.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":502,"aSentId":503},{"question":"Was it just like the unmentionable?","answer":"You just made a record.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":506,"aSentId":507},{"question":"Should it be something that we focus on really, or should we celebrate -- and I sort of instinctively am beginning to feel should we focus more on these incredible songs she sang?","answer":"I think so.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":528,"aSentId":529},{"question":"What is your overview on what\u0027s going on here?","answer":"Unfortunately, Iran is running terror against Israel for many, many years.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":555,"aSentId":556},{"question":"Would Israel go alone?","answer":"HALOM: Israel is trying to stop the military program of Iran for years.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":565,"aSentId":566},{"question":"Has it become a problem for you?","answer":"Every one of us, it doesn\u0027t matter if you\u0027re Israelis, Americans, Europeans, we are in favor of those people that are asking for freedom, for human rights, for liberty.","docId":"120214pmt","qSentId":579,"aSentId":580}]